 media you use. &#160; In some cases you may be surprised and find that they use a niche network such as Etsy, a platform focused on arts and crafts. &#160; Create a profile for you, your company or your blog on the most relevant social networks. Look for forums, communities and interest groups and join them. Keep track of your contacts and messages once a week. &#160; Above all, keep control of your resources and your time. It is better to have a presence in two or three social networks and [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-profile-on-social-networks/">CREATE YOUR PROFILE ON SOCIAL NETWORKS</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Claudio Torres";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3834:"<p>Which social networks should your company join? If you try to get involved with the hundreds of new networks that pop up each month, you will probably make a lot of bad bets and invest resources in platforms that give you no return.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As a small business, your digital marketing should be focused. And your focus is simple: You have to be where your customer is.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>You cannot be everywhere, so consider which networks are most relevant to your customers. If necessary, talk to some of your customers and find out what they use: Facebook, YouTube, Twitter, LinkedIn? It is your customers who will dictate which social media you use.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In some cases you may be surprised and find that they use a niche network such as Etsy, a platform focused on arts and crafts.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Create a profile for you, your company or your blog on the most relevant social networks. Look for forums, communities and interest groups and join them. Keep track of your contacts and messages once a week.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Above all, keep control of your resources and your time. It is better to have a presence in two or three social networks and really relate to their members, than to create dozens of profiles on multiple networks and be unable to maintain those relationships.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Remember that when you put a company profile on a social network, your customers will feel at liberty to write, ask questions and request support through that network. And there is nothing more frustrating than a company profile that gives you no contact response.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Create a professional profile on LinkedIn (<a href="http://www.linkedin.com">www.linkedin.com</a>) for yourself, rather than for your company, and do the same for any other professional network that is appropriate to you. Create an initial network on LinkedIn by including former work and study colleagues and join groups that interest you.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Keep track of your contacts and messages once a week.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>GO BEYOND THE PROFILES</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>You will often need to go beyond creating profiles and exchanging information with your customers. Many social networks allow for the creation of theme-based discussion groups and it is important to participate in those that are of most interest to your company.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>You can take this even further by creating a group based on a subject that linked to your company and leading it. This doesn’t work well for all small businesses, but if you dominate a theme that is linked directly to your business it can be an excellent way of grouping customers and influencers around your company.</p>
<h2>DO NOT SPAM</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Never use social networks for sending mass messages and resist the temptation to advertise openly in your posts.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Remember that you can be blocked from any social network and sending mass advertising is the quickest way to destroy your customer relationships.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>It is much more effective simply to include your name, e-mail and website as a standard signature on any post you make.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Social media is not like conventional media. This isn’t television, radio or a newspaper, where an advertisement has a place. If you want to advertise, use the space and tools that are designed for online advertising. Never advertise via your social network profile or that of your company. We will look at online advertising later in this small business series.</p>
<p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-profile-on-social-networks/">CREATE YOUR PROFILE ON SOCIAL NETWORKS</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-profile-on-social-networks/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"
		
		
		
		
		
				

		
		
			
			
		
