iple blogs on a single screen. &#160; Leave comments whenever you read an interesting post on one of these blogs, adding your email and your website address in the comment signature. This will help raise the profile of your company. &#160; Over time you will make connections with the blogs’ writers and publishers and you will be able to have your links or articles published in them. &#160; Another advantage of this relationship is that you can feed your social media platforms with links to articles in these blogs. Whenever you read something [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/how-to-make-a-map-of-the-blogosphere/">How to make a map of the Blogosphere</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Claudio Torres";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1932:"<p>Make a map of your blogosphere, listing the main blogs that discuss themes that are related to your business and that your customers may also be reading. This is very useful for all digital marketing activities.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Your list should contain at least fifteen blogs related to your business. Find them by searching on Google for related themes and looking at which blogs are most active and appear most frequently in the search results.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Subscribe to the respective feeds for each blog and follow them once a week. A reading tool such as iGoogle (<a href="http://www.google.com/ig">www.google.com/ig</a>) is highly practical for this as it allows you to track multiple blogs on a single screen.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Leave comments whenever you read an interesting post on one of these blogs, adding your email and your website address in the comment signature. This will help raise the profile of your company.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Over time you will make connections with the blogs’ writers and publishers and you will be able to have your links or articles published in them.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Another advantage of this relationship is that you can feed your social media platforms with links to articles in these blogs. Whenever you read something of interest to your audience, you can share the link on your social networks.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Your relationship with bloggers can also help with sales promotions and launches. If you have launched a new product, invite bloggers to try it out. Some blogs may request samples or products to use as prize draws for their readers, which also increases their exposure.</p>
<div></div>
<p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/how-to-make-a-map-of-the-blogosphere/">How to make a map of the Blogosphere</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/how-to-make-a-map-of-the-blogosphere/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"
		
		
		
		
		
				

		
		
			
			
		
		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"CREATE YOUR TWITTER PROFILE";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-twitter-profile/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-twitter-profile/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 20 Feb 2013 09:00:14 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"Internet Marketing for Small Business Series";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/?p=2724";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1106:"<p>Twitter has expanded rapidly as an information center and is now used by your customers, by journalists, by bloggers, and by influencers in your market. It must therefore be one of the basics of your social media marketing strategy. &#160; Create a profile for yourself, your company or your blog on Twitter (www.twitter.com). Search for people who are important to your business and start following them. &#160; Install an application on your blog to tweet your articles (as I mentioned earlier WordPress already offers this as a plugin) and complement it by writing once a day about interesting things that happen with your business. &#160; Twitter is an important tool for viral campaigns and promotions. But leave these until you have an established follower base. Viral campaigns and promotions work best once people have an established relationship with you.</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-twitter-profile/">CREATE YOUR TWITTER PROFILE</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Claudio Torres";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1186:"<p>Twitter has expanded rapidly as an information center and is now used by your customers, by journalists, by bloggers, and by influencers in your market. It must therefore be one of the basics of your social media marketing strategy.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Create a profile for yourself, your company or your blog on Twitter (<a href="http://www.twitter.com">www.twitter.com</a>). Search for people who are important to your business and start following them.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Install an application on your blog to tweet your articles (as I mentioned earlier WordPress already offers this as a plugin) and complement it by writing once a day about interesting things that happen with your business.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Twitter is an important tool for viral campaigns and promotions. But leave these until you have an established follower base. Viral campaigns and promotions work best once people have an established relationship with you.</p>
<p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-twitter-profile/">CREATE YOUR TWITTER PROFILE</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/create-your-twitter-profile/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"
		
		
		
		
		
				

		
		
			
			
		
