on one or two social networks. They may read blogs only occasionally and use email sparingly. So set up your social network profiles and use the articles from your blogs to feed them, and you will increase the exposure of your business. &#160; The content you produce is a good way to start a social media conversation. It is readily accepted, useful for those who are connected to you, and often interesting to relay to your customers’ friends.</p><p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/use-your-blog-on-social-media-marketing/">Use your Blog on Social Media Marketing</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Claudio Torres";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1393:"<p>As we saw in the content marketing section, it is important to create a blog on your company web site and keep it up to date. This facilitates communication and keeps your customers informed.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The vast majority of social networks such as Twitter, Facebook, and LinkedIn offer tools for updating your profile from your blog. So when you publish something new, your customers will be updated via their social media networks.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Furthermore, this makes it much easier for them to relay your content to other people in their network by liking it, re-tweeting it or sharing it</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Note that people often focus just on one or two social networks. They may read blogs only occasionally and use email sparingly. So set up your social network profiles and use the articles from your blogs to feed them, and you will increase the exposure of your business.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The content you produce is a good way to start a social media conversation. It is readily accepted, useful for those who are connected to you, and often interesting to relay to your customers’ friends.</p>
<p>The post <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/use-your-blog-on-social-media-marketing/">Use your Blog on Social Media Marketing</a> appeared first on <a href="http://www.theclaudiotorres.com">Claudio Torres - Digital Marketing and Social Media</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"http://www.theclaudiotorres.com/use-your-blog-on-social-media-marketing/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"
		
		
		
		
		
				

		
		
			
			
		
